\subsection{DDGP}
The reinforcement learning agent is trained using the DDPG algorithm, which combines temporal difference learning and policy gradients. The critic network estimates the Q-function using TD targets, while the actor network is updated through deterministic policy gradients (\cite{cao2020deephedging}, p.10-11). 

\subsection{Twin Delayed Deep Deterministic Policy Gradient (TD3)}
The twin delayed deep deterministic policy gradient (TD3) also uses an actor critic approach, as the DDGP agent, but this algorithm includes some adjustments. The aim of TD3 is to fix some of the issues in the deep deterministic policy gradient. This algorithm handles these issues with 3 main adjustments: clipped double Q-learning, target policy smoothing, and delayed policy updates. Clipped double learning means that two critics are used to estimate the q-function. The agent will use the lowest of the two q-values, which will help with overestimation. Target smoothing also aims to reduce overestimation, which is done by adding random noise to the target action when updating the policy. Delayed policy updates are used to address instability and this is done by updating the policy network less frequently than value networks \footnote{https://medium.com/@joanna.z.gryczka/td3-tutorial-and-implementation-682f16b56699}.



